Highly recommended

Review for: Ba Na Hills Small Group Tour Book now

I loved this trip, and credit goes to our guide Jesmine! The place is beautiful, and a must visit if you're in the area. But it would be almost too crowded to enjoy, if not for Jesmine, who has amazing positive energy, keeping the group engaged and the tour enjoyable. She took nice photos for us, arranged for lunch for our vegan group mates. The thunder stopped the cable cars for a couple hours and as we were stuck, she found a way to the adventure park so we could do something fun instead of waiting in the station. The tour itself was well organised, loved that the tickets were bought in advance, the pickup and drop was smooth. It was a tiring long day, but it was wonderful to experience the 4 seasons in one day at Bana 😁

Chloe
Yesterday
Fantastic

Review for: Ba Na Hills Small Group Tour Book now

Ba Na Hills was really nice and impressive. The place was beautiful, it was cooling which is a nice change from the high temperatures down in Danang. We went to 1) Golden hand Bridge 3/5- There were so many tourists!! we had to snap pictures quickly to avoid having extra people in the photo. It was nice but the amount of people on the bridge made it look like any other bridge. 25mins 2) Đỉnh núi Chúa (?) 3/5 - not sure what the place was called but it was the one with the Buddha Statue. Nice place to walk and look around but nothing really exciting, there is a part where you can take a photo with a nice view. 1.5 hours 3) went for lunch around 12pm.4/5- not too bad some of the dishes were really good, some alright, again, can't help it, it was really crowded on a wednesday. A lot of tourists. 1 hour 4) Sun World Ba Na 2hours -Fantasy theme park 3/5 - Really nice to walk around and play some of the rides! all of them are free unless you want to priority queue at 70K VND (USD 2.89) per ride. Good for Families -French Village 5/5- located same area. it was so beautiful. The chapel here was beautiful, nice for a quick rest stop. buildings were beautiful. the place was amidst the clouds. A Few restuarants and hotels around but i woudlt recommnend staying here, not much to do. Guide: My guide was very knowledgeable and shared with us a lot about Vietnam, not just Ba Na Hills and Danang but where to go in the whole of Vietnam and when is the best time to go and we appreciated that. However, due to language barrier and his tendency for sarcasm, he came off as rude at times. 1) he asked us for our whatsapp so he could contact us in case of emergencies, one of the tourist said that he did not have internet data. The guide replied "thats your problem, not mine:)" 2) Always walked fast in front. lost sight of him a few times. 3) bought a hot dog bun in the early parts of the trip as my partner and i were hungry, we shared it, maybe around 10am. At 12pm, we asked if it time for lunch, the tour guide asked "you're hungry again?" 4)in the bus to Ba Na hills, he introduced a little bit of Ba Na Hills and then asked if we had questions. So i asked if there would be a Cable car ride up as this page did not specifically state there was. and he replied "Okay i am asking if you have any other questions, please listen to me" Never answered my question. When my partner asked another question at a much later point in the bus ride, he said "can you please follow what i am saying?" 5) Never really engaged with us a lot or looked out for us. I felt a little like i was stupid for asking stupid questions, I never asked him any questions after that and actively avoided him. The other tourists in the group, you could visibly see that they were not exactly thrilled too. Pros: knowledgeable and you could tell he enjoyed sharing, left us to our own devices. cons: kinda rude, left us to our own devices. I am sure this is just a one off as we took a different tour from the same company but the guide was great. tour guide unfortunately 2.5/5
